THEZZAZZGLITCH'S BIG TRAINER LIST FOR POKéMON RED/BLUE

This list does not only list all the trainers in the game, but also all (14336 to be exact) of their possible loadouts.

FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS

Q: What is a 'roster #00'? Why is it at the end? A: The game has a small programming error, where loading a roster with id 0 causes the game to load an unexistent roster 256 instead. Since these rosters are different than the others, there's no reason not to include them in this file too.

Q: Which of the rosters cause the ZZAZZ glitch? A: Every roster which has no Pokémon (which is empty).

Q: How can I get these rosters to appear? A: There are 4 ways to do so in Red/Blue:

1. Gameshark. Modify the trainer with 01XX59D0, and change the roster with 01XX5DD0.

2. Mew/Ditto Glitch: Lowering or increasing the attack modifier of a found Ditto will allow you to change the roster of a trainer you will encounter:

    • Growl at Ditto 2 times: Roster 5 will be loaded.
    • Make Ditto uses Swords Dance 1 time: Roster 9 will be loaded.

Of course, you still need a right special stat to make the correct trainer appear.

3. Old Man glitch: Encountering a trainer on Cinnabar coast while still having a loaded roster ID in memory will cause you to fight against a roster of a trainer #256. Trainer class do not change anything in this case:

    • Fight a Rocket with roster 0x0A first, then encounter a trainer on Cinnabar coast - you will fight roster 0x0A of trainer #256.
    • Fight a Channeler with roster 0x03 first, encounter a trainer on Cinnabar coast - you will fight roster 0x03 of trainer #256.

4. 8F: With arbitrary code execution, you can access all 14336 rosters without problem. However, you need to be experienced in Z80 assembly if you think about trying this.

Q: I tried getting a roster from this list using the Old Man glitch, but the roster I got is completely different! A: Encountering trainers from the Cinnabar coast does not work properly - even though you're fighting Prof.Oak/Koga/Rocket, the game still thinks you're fighting a trainer with ID 256.

Q: HOLY CRAP HOW DID YOU MAKE THIS LIST A: I wrote a small C++ program to do all that stuff for me.

Q: How do I open/search this file? It's way too huge. A: First of all, you should get a text editor that allows you to work with big files smoothly. Notepad probably won't do. WordPad is with every Windows computer and works pretty well.

    • If you want to find a specific trainer, just search for this: ">>> TRAINER (insert hex here)"

Then scroll until you see a roster you want. The only exception is the entry for trainer #256, called: ">>> TRAINER 256"

Q: All the ZZAZZ trainers have Charizard 'Ms, but there are no Charizard 'Ms in their rosters.

A: ZZAZZ corrupts many game variables - including a link battle flag, which causes the real roster to be erased. That's why you can't see any real loadouts of the ZZAZZ trainers.

Q: I used a gameshark code to encounter a trainer. The rosters do not appear correctly though. A: Turn off the gameshark codes after the battle starts :)
